# HobiHobby — Current Build Context

## Product Stage
Solo founder. Early MVP. Phase 1 partially live on Vercel (Hobby Explorer + Detail Pages).
No hard launch deadline. Focus is on quality over speed.

## Active Sprint: Sprint 1
Build Firebase Auth end-to-end + save hobbies.

### Sprint 1 Goals
- Backend: Firebase Admin SDK token verification middleware
- Backend: User profile creation in Firestore on first login
- Backend: Save/unsave hobby endpoints (POST/DELETE /api/hobbies/:id/save)
- Frontend (web): Login + Signup screens
- Frontend (web): Auth state in Redux (user slice)
- Frontend (web): Save hobby button wired to backend
- Firestore collections: users, savedHobbies

### Sprint 1 Rules
- Do NOT build community features, the map, or payments yet
- Do NOT add micro-frontend complexity — single web/ React+Vite app only
- Database: Firestore only — no MongoDB, no Mongoose
- Auth: Firebase Auth only — no custom JWT issuing

---

## Roadmap Overview

### Phase 1 — Foundation (current)
Auth, user profiles, save hobbies, onboarding flow

### Phase 2 — AI Hook
AI Hobby Discovery Quiz → OpenAI → ranked recommendations with match score + reasoning
AI Hobby Coach (chat interface, GPT-4 backend)
Tutorial summarization into beginner checklists

### Phase 3 — Retention Engine
365-day hobby journey (progressive daily tasks per hobby)
Streak tracking, weekly milestones, comeback challenges
Progress photo timeline
Personalized AI weekly plans

### Phase 4 — Local Discovery
Hobby Map (Google Maps + Places API)
Nearby classes, workshops, hobby stores
Community Circles (small local groups by hobby + location)

### Phase 5 — Monetization
Freemium gate on Phase 2–3 premium features
Affiliate links (Amazon, Decathlon) on hobby detail pages
Sponsored class/workshop listings

### Phase 6 — Scale
React Native mobile app (Expo)
Push notifications
Offline mode
Social sharing (progress cards, milestone shares)

---

## Architecture Decisions (locked)
- Monorepo: backend/ + web/ + mobile/ + shared/
- NO micro-frontends — single web/ React+Vite app
- Database: Firebase Firestore only (no MongoDB/Mongoose)
- Auth: Firebase Auth + Firebase Admin SDK on backend
- State: Redux Toolkit + Redux Persist
- AI: OpenAI API (Phase 2+) — not yet active
- Payments: Stripe (Phase 5) — not yet active
- Maps: Google Maps + Places API (Phase 4) — not yet active

## Tech Stack (active)
- Frontend: React 18 + Vite + TypeScript + TailwindCSS + Redux Toolkit
- Backend: Express.js + Node.js + Firebase Admin SDK
- Database: Firebase Firestore
- Auth: Firebase Auth
- Hosting: Vercel (web), TBD (backend)

